<div class="content-box">
    <p><strong>GameLog</strong> is a full-stack web application designed for video game enthusiasts. It serves as a personal aggregator where users can discover, save, and review their favorite games.</p>
    
    <h3>Core Technologies</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js with the Express.js framework.</li>
        <li><strong>Database:</strong> MySQL for persistent data storage of users and reviews.</li>
        <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> EJS (Embedded JavaScript) for dynamic server-side rendering of pages.</li>
        <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Session-based authentication using `express-session` with passwords securely hashed by `bcryptjs`.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Features</h3>
    <p>This application was built to fulfill a university project brief, demonstrating a range of web development skills:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Secure user registration and login system.</li>
        <li>Consumption of a third-party REST API (<a href="https://rawg.io/" target="_blank">RAWG.io</a>) to fetch real-time game data.</li>
        <li>Provision of an internal REST API to expose user library data.</li>
        <li>Full CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) functionality for game reviews.</li>
        <li>Database-backed search functionality for a user's personal library.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

